remediation.restart_service:
If a case involves a kubernetes pod, you may be asked to remediate the issue by invoking the specified workflow via the following Kibana API:

```
POST kbn:/api/workflows/{WORKFLOW_ID}/run
{
    "inputs": {
        "service_name": ,
        "service_action": ,
        "case_id": 
    }
}
```

where  is the name of the service,  is  'restart', and `case_id` is the id of the Kibana case likely referenced earlier in this conversation. If it is not available, send "NOT_AVAILABLE" as the `case_id`.
